Mentha rotundifolia

   [15319.jpg]
    Authority   (L.) Huds.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Lamiales:Labiatae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 15319

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Tindall H 1983 pp 245-247 [TEMP, TEXT, FER, DRA, FER, LIG]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 379 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 21 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial herb. First shoots may normally be harvested 40-55 days from
   planting of divided rottstocks.
   COMMON NAMES
   Applemint, Round-leaved mint.
   FURTHER INF
   Altitudes above 1000 m are generally suitable in the tropics.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
